{"title":"WTC Expands Pedal Line with New Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals Designed for Mid-Foot Riding","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-components-ripsaw-aluminum-flat-pedals-convex/","date":1712844000000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"880\" alt=\"(Photos/Wolf Tooth Components)\" /></p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Minnesota machining wizards</a> are at it again with the release of the Ripsaw pedal. This new aluminum pedal has a slim, lightweight design with a slight convex profile and is specifically made for mid-foot riding. The Ripsaw comes following the success of WTC’s <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-components-wtc-waveform-flat-pedal/\" target=\"_blank\">Waveform pedal</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-designed-for-mid-pedal-riders-e1712766998693.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"712\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-designed-for-mid-pedal-riders-e1712766998693.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals designed for mid-pedal riders\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-designed-for-mid-pedal-riders-e1712766998693.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-designed-for-mid-pedal-riders-e1712766998693-297x165.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-designed-for-mid-pedal-riders-e1712766998693-120x67.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-designed-for-mid-pedal-riders-e1712766998693-768x427.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Wolf Tooth Components)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The internals of the pedals include three fully sealed cartridge bearings, a stainless steel axle, an igus bushing, and a custom radial seal protecting internal components against trail muck. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-profile-e1712767039952.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"674\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-profile-e1712767039952.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals profile\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-profile-e1712767039952.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-profile-e1712767039952-297x156.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-profile-e1712767039952-120x63.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-profile-e1712767039952-768x404.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The large machined aluminum platform provides a strong foothold, ideal for all-mountain riding. The thin convex profile is only 7mm thick at the leading edge and tallest at the pedal spindle. WTC says this profile aligns perfectly with the natural arch of the foot and provides a strong platform for power transfer. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ripsaw Pedal Profile</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-convex-e1712767101162.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"691\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-convex-e1712767101162.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals convex\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-convex-e1712767101162.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-convex-e1712767101162-297x160.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-convex-e1712767101162-120x65.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-convex-e1712767101162-768x415.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Being only 12.5mm thick in the center and just 7mm thick in the front and rear edges, the new Ripsaw pedals are sleek, to say the least. It carries a large 118mm x 102mm profile. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals outside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-outside-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This offers support and comfort for all riders but performs exceptionally well for riders who prefer a mid-foot pedal position. This design benefits those riders whose shoes don’t have much structure or support. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Colors and Pedal Pins </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals colors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-colors-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Ripsaw pedal comes in three colors, Raw Silver, Ultraviolet Purple, and Black. There are 12 stainless steel, rear-loading, 4.5mm pins on each side of the pedal offering a boatload of traction. There are an additional six 4.5mm and six 3mm pins that ship with the pedals. These are also available as replacement parts. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-closeup-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The shorter pins are included so the rider can customize the amount of convexity the pedal has. For instance, if you install the shorter pins on the edges of the Ripsaw, the convex profile will be emphasized. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ripsaw Internals</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals spindle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-spindle-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I think we can all agree that quality internal components are essential for our components to have a long performance life. Inside the new Ripsaw pedal is a machined 17-4 stainless steel axle. and as mentioned earlier, it sports three low-friction, fully sealed cartridge bearings, and one igus bushing. It uses a custom radius seal to protect the internals from harmful trail debris. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the same internals that WTC uses on the popular Waveform Aluminum Pedals. Those pedals have been earning positive, long-term reviews for superior performance in all conditions. So, the new Ripsaw will give you consistent, reliable performance while riding in the rain, mud, sand, dirt, and snow. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Made in ‘Merica</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals steps\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-steps-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ripsaw aluminum pedals are designed, engineered, machined, and assembled at Wolf Tooth in Minnesota, USA. Each pedal body starts as a solid 6061-T6 aluminum billet. It then spends 40 minutes in a CNC mill where the 118mm x 102mm platform finds its shape. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals on the machine\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-the-machine-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals parts and bits\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-and-bits-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals parts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-parts-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Meanwhile, over in axle land, the 17-4 stainless steel axles start as long cylindrical rods getting fed into a CNC lathe to get cut into their final form. All of the 33 individual components are compiled and assembled. The assembly of the many parts happens within 40 feet of the source CNC machines. They are then packed and shipped to eager cyclists around the globe. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Ripsaw Fully Repairable</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-rebuildable-e1712767380369.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"588\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-rebuildable-e1712767380369.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals rebuildable\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-rebuildable-e1712767380369.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-rebuildable-e1712767380369-297x136.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-rebuildable-e1712767380369-120x55.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-rebuildable-e1712767380369-768x353.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wolf Tooth believes in the Right to Repair. So, all individual components of the Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals are available as replacement parts. That includes the pedal body, stainless steel axle, bearings, and more. Along with the included six additional pins, is an owner’s manual, and video guide that’s provided on the Waveform Aluminum Pedal webpage for customers to disassemble, service, and reassemble the pedals at home. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet.jpeg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals on billet\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Wolf-Tooth-Ripsaw-Aluminum-Pedals-on-billet-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals carry a 5-year warranty that covers defects in material and workmanship from the date of purchase. The pedals can also be sent to Wolf Tooth for service. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Availability and Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $199 (per set)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals Press Release</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals are available today at the link below and at any bike shop that stocks Wolf Tooth.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">WolfToothComponents.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-components-ripsaw-aluminum-flat-pedals-convex/\">WTC Expands Pedal Line with New Ripsaw Aluminum Pedals Designed for Mid-Foot Riding</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"67212b843d9d51f02940116a04f9bda7bcbdb191dfe1a549dc29f8a589a02293","category":"Cycling"}